The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) has decided to set up a databank of all age-groups and appoint separate video analysts for each group. Starting from under-16 side, the under-19 and under-22 sides will also have a video analyst, a first for any association in the country.           
	 The National Cricket Academy (NCA) Level A refresher course for coaches will be held at the Eden from Friday. About 24 Level-A coaches from different states will participate in the three-day long course that concludes Sunday.           
	 Mohun Bagan blanked Army XI 3-0 in a friendly match at their home ground on Thursday. Edeh Chidi, Tomba Singh and Suraj Mondal scored a goal each.          
	 Former JCT forward Edu is expected to play for Mohammedan Sporting. Club officials Thursday confirmed that the Brazilian would don the clubs jersey in the upcoming IFA Shield.          
	 Atishay Ajmera of Rajasthan caused an upset when he defeated IM V. Saravanan in a opening round game of the 47th edition of the National B Chess Championship, being held at the Town Hall on Thursday.                                                                                                                                                                        
